<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1151> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1151" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "They celebrated as Proconsuls naval triumphs over Cossyra and the Carthaginians (Act. Tr., Degrassi, 76f., 548)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1147> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1147" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Polyb. 1.36.10; Liv. 42.20.1; Eutrop. 2.22; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Oros. 4.9.5; Cassiod.; Zon. 8.14; see Degrassi, 42f., 116, 434f. The Consuls brought a fleet to evacuate the survivors of Regulus' army, routed a Punic fleet off Cape Bon, and captured Cossyra, but suffered a disastrous shipwreck off Camarina (Polyb. 1.36.10-37; Eutrop. 2.22; Oros. 4.9.5-8; Zon. 8.14; cf. Diod. 23.18; Liv. Per. 18)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10101> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10101" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Naval Triumph de Cossurensibus et Poeneis. MRR I.210, Itgenshorst no. 135, Rich no. 134." .
